    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAs the title says, In `nvim_buf_add_highlight()`, since -1 can be specified as `{col}` (or `{col_end}` in `nvim_buf_add_highlight()`), it is lack coherence to not be able to use -1 in `{opts}.end_col`.\r\nIt should be fixed by tweaking this area.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/a376d979bda103fa9998d05c3cc4ba56d3c3cece/src/nvim/api/extmark.c#L556\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:call setline(1, 'foo')\r\n:call nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, nvim_create_namespace('foo'), 0, 0, #{ end_row: 0, end_col: -1, hl_group: 'Error' })\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAdd highlight to the first line.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-a376d97\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04.5 LTS (WSL2)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWindows terminal\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
